-- Microsoft's Xbox Tops U.S. Retail Console Sales in May
-- B y   C l i f f   E d w a r d s
-- 2013-06-17T22:30:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-17/microsoft-s-xbox-tops-u-s-retail-console-sales-in-may.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  said U.S. retailers
sold 114,000 Xbox 360 game consoles in May, helping it retain
the top-selling spot for the 29th straight month.  Spending in May on all Xbox products, including the
console, Kinect motion-sensing peripheral and software totaled
$149.8 million, Redmond, Washington-based Microsoft said today
in an e-mail, citing NPD Group Inc. data.  Sales of the console fell 29 percent compared with a year
earlier, when it sold 160,000 units.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cliff Edwards in San Francisco at 
 cedwards28@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
